<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-05T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="514" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d514">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.01/53a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-05T14:00:00-05:00">December 5, 1933—2
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>38. The President said today to say to you that in the event other
                                Latin American nations desire to recognize the present Cuban
                                authorities, we should not attempt to block them; that meanwhile, we
                                should stand by the policy set forth in his Warm Springs statement
                                but should be prepared to consider developments in order to
                                determine whether the situation at any future time fulfills the
                                criteria of recognition maintained in that statement.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>